0.title: Becoming a Monster Rules
0.body:
Nefarious: Becoming a Monster Expansion;

I recommend not adding the expansion until you (and everyone you're playing with) is familiar with how the game works, since there are many new mechanics added that can be confusing to new players. I'd recommend about 7-10 games before adding the expansion.

Contents:
1: 3 new actions (for each player),
2: 3 new 'role' cards.
3: 21 new inventions
4: 25 new twists.
4: turn tracker token (small circular brain token) 
5: turn tracking and victory point tracking board. 

To Play:

Start by opening up the white bag labelled Becoming a Monster next to the board and remove all of the components.

Set aside all the new action and role cards. These will not be used unless a 'new twist' says so.

 Just like the base game, we start by drawing two twists (either from just the expansion, or shuffled in with the base game) and placing them on the two twist spaces on the board.


After reading the twists, get out any of the new components that will be required, if any. 

New cards:
these actions are resolved in number order, just like the base game.

5: Develop; 
Discard an already played invention and play a new one (from your hand), subracting 5 coins per VP your discarded invention is worth.

6: Experiment;
Draw an invention card,  you may play it immediatly (if you can afford it), otherwise keep the card in your hand and do nothing else this turn.

7: Produce;
Gain 2 coins for each played invention of the player with the most inventions.

new roles:
If one (or more) of the role cards is requierd by a twist, find the appropriate one from the new gray cards.

Police;
Before playing a card, the player with the "police" card will declare an action card type that cannot be played that turn. The police card then passes to the player on the left who will then declare at the start of the next turn. It is up to you (and friends) whether to allow the same action  to be prohibited two (or more) times in a row.

Orphan;
At the beginning of every turn, the player holding the "orphan" card will lose 1 coin (before playing an action), the player can pass along the orphan card only if they play "research" as their action. The card then passes left to the next player who did not also play "research". If all players play research, the card is passed to the first player on the left of the card owner.

Mole;
Spies get double profit for the card owner (only on the 4 main zones). Then the card is passed to the next plauer on the left.


New ORANGE Invention type:
The new orange inventions have repeatable effects. They are tied to a basic action card type and can only be collected on the following turn after they are played (they have no immediate effect).



Investment Zones:
Some of the new twists are called investment zones, which means that for a cost, (specified on the twist) you may place a spy on the twist card and perform it's benefit when it instructs you to do so.

Special rules for your spies:
When a player plays the "Develop" card, this triggers the "Invent" zone for spies.

When a player plays the "Experiment" card, this triggers the "Research" zone for spies.

When a player plays the "Produce" card, this triggers the "Work" zone for spies.
